{"TopicId":145144,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Placing RCS Thrusters in advanced construction tutorial - can\u0026#039;t continue!","CreatedByName":"wafu_tony","CreatedById":167265,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-31T11:15:31Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"wafu_tony","CreatedById":167265,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-31T11:15:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHey,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is probably a really stupid noob question, but I\u0027m stuck in the advanced construction tutorial whilst placing the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E thrusters!! I\u0027ve followed the steps - added 4 symmetrical thrusters on the FL-T100 tank, moved them with the offset tool, reset them using space, and then turned off the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E indicator but it won;t let me click \u0022Next\u0022. Not sure what I\u0027m doing wrong! I\u0027ll try and insert a picture below:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://flic.kr/p/JJXhB3\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022https://c1.staticflickr.com/9/8580/28053064104_c5c55f009e_h.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 alt=\u002228053064104_c5c55f009e_h.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://flic.kr/p/JJXhB3\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E2016-07-31\u003C/a\u003E by \u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.flickr.com/photos/cocksy/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EAnthony Cocks\u003C/a\u003E, on Flickr\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-07-31T11:16:15Z\u0022 title=\u002207/31/2016 11:16  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 31, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by wafu_tony\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sebi.zzr","CreatedById":81294,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-31T12:58:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUse the offset tool to place \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E bloks in to the right place:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://imgur.com/a/9t0uD\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://imgur.com/a/9t0uD\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv data-role=\u0022contentPage\u0022\u003E\n\u003Chr data-role=\u0022contentPageBreak\u0022\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"wafu_tony","CreatedById":167265,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-31T13:02:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks. I restarted the tutorial and it worked fine the next time!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Reactordrone","CreatedById":110060,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-31T13:34:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou could try selecting and de-selecting the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E indicator.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"BayesianBits","CreatedById":183546,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-12-15T08:51:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRefill your fuel tanks.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DankMemes","CreatedById":184031,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-01-01T20:24:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBefore clicking Next, turn off the Center of Mass Overlay. That fixed it for me.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"blazeline","CreatedById":197853,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-02T19:18:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nModifying a fuel level enabled the Next button for me.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}